		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Mudra</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about the use of mudrā in Indic religion.  For mudra as used in Indian classical music, see <a href="/wiki/Mudra_(music)" title="Mudra (music)">Mudra (music)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Namaste1.jpg" class="image" title="Woman performing namaskaram mudrā"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Namaste1.jpg/180px-Namaste1.jpg" width="180" height="386" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Namaste1.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Woman performing <a href="/wiki/Namaskaram" title="Namaskaram" class="mw-redirect">namaskaram</a> mudrā</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A <b>mudrā</b> (<a href="/wiki/Sanskrit" title="Sanskrit">Sanskrit</a>: मुद्रा, lit. "seal") is a symbolic or ritual gesture in <a href="/wiki/Hinduism" title="Hinduism">Hinduism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhism</a>. While some mudrās involve the entire body, most are performed with the hands and fingers. Mudrā (<a href="/wiki/Sanskrit" title="Sanskrit">Sanskrit</a>) is "spiritual gesture" and energetic "seal of authenticity" employed in the <a href="/wiki/Iconography" title="Iconography">iconography</a> and <a href="/wiki/Spiritual_practice" title="Spiritual practice">spiritual practice</a> of <a href="/wiki/Indian_religions" title="Indian religions">Indian religions</a> and <a href="/wiki/Taoism" title="Taoism">Taoism</a>.</p>
